textAfterTable: Friess appeared in 30 games, making 14 starts, in her freshman season with the Matadors … averaged 2.6 points and 3.1 rebounds for the season … scored a season-high eight points in road win at UC Riverside … knocked down season-high two 3-pointers in road win at UC Irvine … had season-high four free throws in loss to Long Beach State … had a season-high nine rebounds in two games … dished out three assists in home win over Pacific … had a season-high two blocks in road win at Cal State Fullerton … had a season-high four steals in two games … finished the year with 17 assists, four blocks and 22 steals in 501 minutes of action.  Savannah Christian High School Randi Friess played four years of volleyball and basketball at for the Raiders ... a two-time member of the GHSA All-State Basketball First Team ... also participated in Converse All Star Classic National Team ... four-time Scholar Athlete ...helped lead the Raiders to the GHSA Class A state championship game in her junior year ...earned all-region honors following all four of her seasons and was all-area her final three years ... graduated in 2011.
